    tag: "Home",
    summary: "Charming home in Tallahassee with fully fenced backyard, minutes from FSU, FAMU, and Midtown dining. Perfect for families, groups, game-day weekends at Doak Campbell Stadium, and graduations.\n\nQuiet Hansell Hill neighborhood near downtown Tallahassee, Cascades Park, and Thomasville Road restaurants. Fully equipped kitchen, high-speed WiFi, and free parking. Close to nature trails, lakes, and Wakulla Springs State Park.",
    description: "✈️ Tallahassee InternatiInternational Airport is\n27 minutes (17.0 miles) away by car\nor taxi\n\nTHINGS-TO-DO\n✔️ Springtime Tallahassee Parade is\ntypically held in March every year.\nOne of the biggest southeastern\nparade and craft show.\n\n✔️ Tallahassee Automobile Museum is a\nmust for car and antique enthusiasts.\n\n✔️ Tallahassee Museum is a 52-acre\nlakeside site featuring zip line tours,\nnature trails, wildlife, period exhibits\nand events. Tree-to-Tree zip line has\n47 platforms, 25 obstacles and 16\nziplines\n\n✔️ FSU Flying High Circus is a unique\ncollegiate tradition with in-air and on-the-ground performances. For all age groups.\n\n✔️ The Museum of Florida History is located\nin downtown Tallahassee and features\nartifacts dating back to 12,000 years.\n\n✔️ Lake Ella and Fred Drake Park.\nWalking and jogging park with scenic\nviews and picnicking. Seasonal\ncelebrations, festivals and craft fairs\nheld here\n\n✔️ Railroad Square Art District. A vibrant\narea of art galleries, studios, shops\nand cultural events. Unique boutiques\noffering vintage items and handmade\ncrafts.\n\n✔️ Florida Historic Capitol Museum is\ntucked away in the old capitol building\nat the heart of the state capitol.\n\n\n🍻PLACES TO DRINK🍻\n🥂 BAR 1903 - Cocktail Bar\n209 E. Park Ave\n\n🥂 LIBERTY - Cocktails, Beer & Wine\n1307 N. Monroe St.\n\n🥂 HUMMINGBIRD WINE BAR - Wine & Cocktails\n1216-4 N. Monroe St.\n\n🥂 BLACK RADISH - Natural Wines & Craft Cocktails\n1304 N. Monroe St, Unit B\n\n🥂 WARHORSE WHISKEY BAR - Cocktails & Whiskey\n603 W. Gaines St.\n\n🍽️PLACES TO EAT🍽️\n🍴 TABLE 23 - Southern-style fare\n1214 Thomasville Road\n\n🍴 MASA - Asian Food\n1605 N. Monroe St\n\n🍴 KOOL BEANZ CAFE - Eclective American Menu\n921 Thomasville Road\n\n🍴 SAVOUR - Gourmet\n115 E. Park. Ave\n\n🍴 BELLA BELLA - Italian\n123 East 5th Ave\n\nYou will have access to the entire home and all of its amenities.\n\nSelf check-in via smart lock for flexible arrival. Our hosting team is available 24/7 via the Airbnb app or phone. We provide full privacy during your stay and respond promptly to any questions or requests. Happy to share local dining recommendations and tips for exploring the area.\n\nDiscover the Best of Tallahassee’s Hansell Hill Neighborhood\n\nHansell Hill is a hidden gem in Tallahassee, offering a serene escape while being just a stone's throw from the city’s top attractions. This peaceful, tree-lined neighborhood is perfect for those looking to experience the charm of a quiet residential area with the convenience of urban living.\n\nProximity to Major Attractions Located just minutes from downtown Tallahassee, Hansell Hill provides easy access to the heart of the city. Florida State University is a quick drive away, making this an ideal spot for visiting parents, alumni, or those attending university events. Midtown Tallahassee, known for its vibrant dining and nightlife, is also nearby, offering an array of restaurants, bars, and local shops to explore.\n\nOutdoor Activities For nature lovers, Hansell Hill is close to several beautiful parks and outdoor spaces. Take a short drive to Cascades Park, a popular spot for walking, picnicking, and enjoying live events. Alfred B. Maclay Gardens State Park is also within reach, offering scenic trails, gardens, and opportunities for boating and fishing.\n\nLocal Dining and Shopping The neighborhood is surrounded by local eateries, coffee shops, and boutique stores, providing plenty of options for dining and shopping without venturing far from home. From casual bites to upscale dining, you’ll find something to suit every taste.\n\nQuiet and Safe Hansell Hill is known for its quiet, family-friendly atmosphere. The streets are safe and well-maintained, making it a great place for evening strolls or morning jogs. Whether you're visiting for a short stay or an extended visit, you’ll appreciate the peaceful ambiance that Hansell Hill has to offer.\n\nExperience the Best of Both Worlds At Hansell Hill, you get the best of both worlds—a tranquil retreat in a welcoming neighborhood with quick access to Tallahassee's bustling city life. It's the perfect base for exploring everything this vibrant city has to offer.\n\n🅿️ PARKING 🅿️\nYou can use the garage or the driveway to park your vehicles. There's NO garage door opener available.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 5th guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 4 guests.",
