    description: "Here are some popular establishments and attractions near the house.\n\n🌊 BEACH 🌊\nFort Lauderdale City Beach is just 10 minutes away.\n\n🍺 PUBS & BARS 🍺\n- The Pub Wilton Manors: A lively spot known for its friendly atmosphere and regular events.\n\n- Georgie's Alibi Monkey Bar: A popular venue offering a mix of entertainment and dining options.\n\n\n🍽️ RESTAURANTS 🍽️\n- La Birria Burger Bar: home of the most awarded burger 🍔 in the world\n\n- Rosie's Bar & Grill: Renowned for its boozy Sunday brunches and festive patio.\n\n- La Mexicana Taco Bar: Offers quality Mexican cuisine in a stunning bohemian setting.\n\n- Tee Jay Thai Sushi: A favorite for Thai and sushi dishes.\n\n\n🛒 GROCERY STORES🛒\n- Publix Super Market at Five Points Plaza: A well-known supermarket chain offering a wide range of products.\n\n- ALDI: A discount grocery store known for its quality products and low prices.\n\n- CVS Pharmacy: Offers a variety of grocery items alongside pharmacy services.\n\n\n👀 TOURIST ATTRACTIONS 👀\nWilton Drive: The main thoroughfare teeming with an array of restaurants, shops, bars, and art galleries.\n\nRichardson Historic Park and Nature Preserve: Offers nature trails and a glimpse into the area's history.\n\nInternational Swimming Hall of Fame: Serves as the central point for the study of the history of swimming in the United States and around the world.\n\n- 11 miles from Hard Rock Hotel\n\nGuest will have access to the entire home and all the amenities in it.\n\nWilton Manors is a dynamic and welcoming community known for its lively atmosphere and diverse culture. Located in the heart of South Florida, this charming neighborhood is packed with vibrant energy, making it a hotspot for locals and visitors alike.\n\nThe area is centered around Wilton Drive, the main thoroughfare that offers an eclectic mix of trendy restaurants, cozy cafes, unique boutiques, and buzzing nightlife. Whether you’re seeking a laid-back meal, an evening out with friends, or a leisurely stroll, Wilton Drive has something for everyone.\n\nNature lovers will appreciate the Richardson Historic Park and Nature Preserve, where you can enjoy peaceful walking trails, lush greenery, and glimpses of local wildlife. For those interested in history and education, the World AIDS Museum and Educational Center is a must-visit, offering thought-provoking exhibits and programs.\n\nThe neighborhood is also conveniently located near Fort Lauderdale’s stunning beaches, cultural landmarks, and international airport, making it an ideal hub for exploring the best of South Florida. Known for its inclusive spirit and vibrant community events, Wilton Manors is the perfect place to experience a blend of relaxation, excitement, and connection.\n\nWhether you're a foodie, a nightlife enthusiast, or someone who enjoys the outdoors, Wilton Manors has it all!\n\nUber and Lyft will be the best way to move around the area if you're not driving.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 4th guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 3 guests.",
