    summary: "A delightful home nestled in the heart of Calera, Oklahoma! Our pet-friendly property is the perfect retreat for families, couples, or anyone seeking a cozy and convenient living space.\n\nThe fully fenced backyard is a standout feature, offering a secure & spacious area for pets to roam freely or for hosting outdoor gatherings. \n\nWhether you’re enjoying a morning coffee on the patio, playing fetch with your pet, or hosting a weekend BBQ, this backyard is designed for relaxation and enjoyment!",
    description: "NEARBY RESTAURANTS\n\nMAGNOLIA CAFE\nA local favorite is known for its cozy atmosphere and delicious comfort food.\n\nOLD ICE HOUSE\nOffers a delightful menu and a welcoming bar atmosphere, perfect for lunch, dinner, or after-dinner drinks.\n\nFLY BREAD EXPRESS\nSpecializes in Native American cuisine, offering a unique dining experience with their signature fry bread dishes. \n\n1832 STEAKHOUSE\nAn upscale dining option for steak lovers, known for its premium cuts and elegant ambiance.\n\nGUY FIERI'S AMERICAN KITCHEN & BAR\nA vibrant spot offering American comfort food with a twist, inspired by celebrity chef Guy Fieri.\n\n\nNEARBY GROCERY STORE\nDollar General\nLocation: 607 S Service Rd, Calera, OK 74730\nDistance: Approximately 0.7 miles (2 minutes by car)\n\nWalmart Supercenter\nLocation: 3712 W Main St, Durant, OK 74701\nDistance: Approximately 7.2 miles (10 minutes by car)\n\nPruett’s Food\nLocation: 1231 N Washington Ave, Durant, OK 74701\nDistance: Approximately 7.1 miles (10 minutes by car)\n\nGreen Spray\nLocation: 429 W Main St, Durant, OK 74701\nDistance: Approximately 6.7 miles (9 minutes by car)\n\nGuest will have private access to the entire house and all of its amenities.\n\nThe guest can reach out anytime for any questions.\n\nNestled in southeastern Oklahoma, Calera is a quaint and charming town offering a welcoming atmosphere and a strong sense of community. Located just off Highway 69/75, it provides convenient access to the neighboring city of Durant and the Texas border, making it an ideal location for those seeking small-town living with big-city conveniences nearby.\n\nThe neighborhood surrounding our home boasts a friendly and safe environment, perfect for families, couples, and pet owners alike. Main Street is the heart of Calera, where you’ll find a mix of local businesses, restaurants, and community events. This area offers a laid-back lifestyle with plenty of green spaces and quiet streets for leisurely walks or outdoor activities.\n\nCalera residents enjoy proximity to excellent schools within the Calera Public School District, as well as nearby attractions such as Choctaw Casino & Resort in Durant, Lake Texoma for outdoor recreation, and the historic Three Valley Museum.\n\nThe town offers everyday conveniences like grocery stores, local dining spots, and shops, while larger retail outlets and specialty stores are just a short drive away in Durant.\n\nWhether you’re looking to settle into a close-knit community, enjoy outdoor adventures, or simply experience the charm of small-town living, Calera is a wonderful place to call home!\n\nUber and Lyft will be your best bet if you're not driving.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 5th guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 4 guests.",
