    description: "The expansive living room opens to a private balcony, perfect for relaxing or entertaining. Additionally, the property boasts a two-car garage, providing ample parking and storage space.\n\n\nNEARBY ATTRACTIONS\nMaple Landing\n- A casual neighborhood bar specializing in bourbon, beer, burgers, and brisket, located in the Medical District. \n\nRESTAURANTS\n🍖 The Landmark Prime Rib\nLocated within the historic Warwick Melrose Hotel, this modern steakhouse offers a blend of tradition and innovation in a century-old setting.\n\n🍖 The Landmark Prime Rib\nLocated within the historic Warwick Melrose Hotel, this modern steakhouse offers a blend of tradition and innovation in a century-old setting.\n\n🍖 City Tavern\nA staple for Dallas locals, this restaurant and bar serves fresh drinks, brunch, lunch, and dinner, with an inviting outdoor patio.\n\n🍕 Bryan Street Tavern\nKnown for exceptional pizza and 22 craft beers on tap, this spot also features one of Dallas' best-known patios, along with pool, darts, and shuffleboard.\n\nPLACES-TO-GO\n📍Greenville Avenue\nA vibrant area near downtown Dallas, offering a variety of restaurants and bars, particularly in the 'Lower Greenville' section.\n\n📍 Exposition Park\nA budding arts district home to eclectic bars, restaurants, art galleries, and performance venues, making it a cultural hotspot.\n\n📍The Stoneleigh P\nA historic bar and grill in the Uptown neighborhood, known for its rich history and recognizable red neon sign.\n\nThe guest will have an exclusive access to the entire place during their private.\n\nGuests can contact us via Airbnb, text, or calls for any questions or assistance anytime.\n\nNestled in a quiet yet convenient area of Dallas, this property offers the perfect blend of suburban tranquility and city accessibility. Located just minutes from downtown, this neighborhood provides easy access to major highways, making commuting and exploring the city a breeze.\n\nEnjoy a variety of nearby dining options, from local favorites to trendy eateries, as well as shopping centers and grocery stores for everyday essentials. Nature lovers will appreciate the green spaces and parks in the area, perfect for a morning jog or a relaxing stroll. With well-maintained streets and a welcoming community, this location is ideal for both short-term visitors and long-term stays.\n\nWhether you're in town for business, leisure, or an extended stay, our home places you in the heart of it all while still offering a peaceful retreat.\n\nUber and Lyft are your best bet to move around.\n\n✅ 12-minute drive from American Airlines Arena\n\n✅ Garage opener available.\n\n✅ Security cameras that monitor the driveway for the entire compound for your security.\n\n✅ Self-check-in using smart locks.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 3rd guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 2 guests.",
