    tag: "LA Home",
    summary: "Spacious 3-story, 4BR home in Minneapolis with basketball court, pickleball court, and karaoke room. Sleeps 12 - perfect for families, groups, and celebrations.\n\nBig backyard with sports courts, fully equipped kitchen, and modern living spaces throughout. Near Downtown Minneapolis, U.S. Bank Stadium, Target Center, Target Field, University of Minnesota, and Mall of America. Easy access to lakes, parks, and the Minneapolis nightlife scene. Free parking and high-speed WiFi.",
    description: "❊ TOP AMENITIES ❊\n‣ Backyard Basketball Court\n‣ Karaoke Machine\n‣ Bluetooth Movie Projector \n‣ Pickleball \n‣ Foosball Table \n‣ Indoor Toddler Swing + Children Books + Chalkboard Wall\n‣ Board Games\n‣ Amazon Alexa\n‣ Diffusers in Every Room + Essential Oils\n‣ Outdoor Fire Pit\n‣ Fully Stocked Kitchen\n\nMake lasting memories in our Family-Friendly 4-Bedroom Home nestled in a quiet neighborhood of Minneapolis, Minnesota. With ample space, a fully equipped kitchen, and a backyard oasis, this welcoming retreat is designed with families in mind, ensuring a comfortable and enjoyable stay for guests of all ages. With a Walkability score of 84, your next adventure can be just steps away! \n\n\n❖ NEARBY FOOD + RESTAURANTS ❖\n• Dunkin' Donuts - (0.1 miles away)\n• Flynn's Eats - (0.1 miles away)\n• Sandy's Tavern - (0.1 miles away)\n• Tazzah Mediterranean - (0.1 miles away)\n• Cadao Express Pho and Vietnamese - (0.2 miles away)\n• Taqueria Limon Mexican - (0.2 miles away)\n\n❖ NEARBY GROCERY STORES ❖\n• CVS Pharmacy - (0.2 miles away)\n• Cub Foods - (0.6 miles away)\n• Target - (1.1 miles away)\n• Aldi - (1.3 miles away)\n• Lunds & Byerlys - (1.7 miles away)\n• Walmart Supercenter - (2.3 miles away)\n\n\n◉ THINGS TO DO ◉\n\n▶︎ Mall of America: Located just a short drive away in Bloomington, the Mall of America is a massive shopping and entertainment complex. It features hundreds of stores, restaurants, a theme park called Nickelodeon Universe, and the SEA LIFE Minnesota Aquarium.\n\n▶︎ U.S. Bank Stadium: Home of The Minnesota Vikings! Only a 12 minute drive from our home!\n\n▶︎ Wood Lake Nature Center: Explore the beautiful natural surroundings at Wood Lake Nature Center. This urban nature oasis offers trails, boardwalks, and wildlife viewing opportunities.\n\n▶︎ Stone Arch Bridge: Enjoy clear views of the Minneapolis skyline and stunning views of the Mississippi River from this Historical Bridge. Take a stroll or rent bikes or scooters to cross. This former railroad bridge is nearly 140 years old. Here, panoramic views of St. Anthony Falls will take your breath away!\n\n\n▶︎ Richfield Outdoor Pool: If you're visiting during the summer months, cool off at the Richfield Outdoor Pool. Enjoy swimming, sunbathing, and various water activities.\n\n▶︎ Lake Harriet: Head to Lake Harriet in Minneapolis for a peaceful retreat. You can walk or bike around the lake, rent paddleboats, or relax on the sandy beach.\n\n▶︎ Minnesota Valley National Wildlife Refuge: Explore the Minnesota Valley National Wildlife Refuge, which offers scenic trails, birdwatching opportunities, and a chance to connect with nature.\n\n▶︎ Mini Golf at Centennial Lakes Park: Enjoy a round of mini-golf at Centennial Lakes Park in Edina. The park also offers paddleboat rentals, walking paths, and beautiful gardens.\n\n▶︎ Fort Snelling State Park: Located near the confluence of the Mississippi and Minnesota rivers, Fort Snelling State Park offers hiking trails, picnic areas, and historical sites such as the Fort Snelling National Historic Landmark.\n\n▶︎ Richfield Farmers Market: Visit the Richfield Farmers Market for fresh produce, local products, and a chance to support local farmers and artisans. The market operates during the summer months.\n\nSelf check-in via smart lock for flexible arrival. Our hosting team is available 24/7 via the Airbnb app or phone. We provide full privacy during your stay and respond promptly to any questions or requests. Happy to share local dining recommendations and tips for exploring the area.\n\nNearby attractions:\n- Downtown Minneapolis (10 min)\n- U.S. Bank Stadium / Vikings (10 min)\n- Target Center / Timberwolves (10 min)\n- Target Field / Twins (10 min)\n- University of Minnesota (10 min)\n- Mall of America (20 min)\n- Minneapolis Chain of Lakes (10 min)\n- North Loop dining district (10 min)\n- Minneapolis-St. Paul Airport (20 min)\n- St. Paul downtown (15 min)\n\nPet friendly: $240/pet per stay.\nGuests must be 25+ to book.\n\nExtra guest fee: $20/guest per night from the 5th guest onwards. Base price covers first 4 guests.",
