    tag: "LA Home",
    summary: "Brand-new 3BR home in Los Angeles near Koreatown, minutes from Universal Studios, Hollywood, DTLA, and LA beaches. Sleeps 8 - ideal for families, groups, and business travelers.\n\nModern 2-story layout with 3 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, fully equipped kitchen, and high-speed WiFi. Easy access to the Hollywood Walk of Fame, Griffith Observatory, Dodger Stadium, LA Convention Center, USC, and the Metro. Free parking included.",
    description: "The space\nOur spacious home comfortably accommodates up to 8 guests with 3 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms. Enjoy modern amenities, a private balcony, and a stylish second-story loft featuring a movie projector—perfect for cozy movie nights.\n\nWhether you're exploring the city or relaxing at home, this is the perfect place for your LA getaway!\n\n🍜 RESTAURANTS 🍜\n- Gus's World Famous Fried Chicken\nRenowned for its spicy fried chicken and Southern-style sides, this eatery offers a casual dining experience.\n\n- Anju House\nA Korean-inspired restaurant serving traditional dishes with a modern twist.\n\n- Lucia Mediterranean Grill\nOffers a variety of Mediterranean dishes, including grilled meats and fresh salads.\n\n- Cass Town\nLocated in Koreatown, this spot is known for its diverse menu and cozy ambiance.\n\n- Shins Pizza\nKnown for its delightful mortadella slice on a garlicky ricotta base, served in a casual setting.\n\n👀 TOURST ATTRACTIONS 👀\n- Universal Studios Hollywood\nA world-famous theme park and working movie studio, featuring thrilling rides, live shows, and the iconic Wizarding World of Harry Potter.\n\n- The Grove\nAn outdoor shopping and entertainment complex offering a mix of retail, dining, and entertainment options.\n\n- Los Angeles County Museum of Art (LACMA)\nThe largest art museum in the western United States, featuring a diverse collection spanning various cultures and time periods.\n\n- La Brea Tar Pits and Museum\nA unique paleontological site where natural asphalt has preserved the bones of prehistoric animals.\n\n- Hollywood Walk of Fame\nFamous sidewalk honoring celebrities from the entertainment industry with embedded stars.\n\n\n🍻 PUBS 🍻\n- Cafe Brass Monkey\nA karaoke dive bar and restaurant in Koreatown, known for its lively atmosphere and history dating back to 1971.\n\n- Boardner's\nA historic bar in Hollywood, established in 1942, known for its film noir atmosphere and popularity within the entertainment industry.\n\n- Tam O'Shanter Inn\nOne of Los Angeles' oldest restaurants, established in 1922, offering hearty pub fare with a Scottish flair.\n\n- Everson Royce Bar\nLocated in the Arts District, this bar is known for its curated selection of drinks and a relaxed outdoor patio.\n\n- Good Clean Fun\nA wine bar in Downtown LA offering a selection of natural wines and light bites in a casual setting.\n\n📍 KEY PLACES 📍\n- Koreatown\nA vibrant neighborhood known for its Korean BBQ restaurants, nightlife, and cultural landmarks.\n\n- Larchmont Village\nA quaint neighborhood offering boutique shops, cafes, and a charming small-town feel.\n\n- Hancock Park\nA historic residential area featuring stately homes and proximity to museums and cultural sites.\n\n- Downtown Los Angeles (DTLA)\nThe city's central business district, offering a mix of historic landmarks, modern skyscrapers, and diverse dining options.\n\n- Melrose Avenue\nA famous street known for its eclectic shops, street art, and trendy eateries.\n\nThe guest will have access to the entire house and all of its amenities.\n\nSelf check-in via smart lock for flexible arrival. Our hosting team is available 24/7 via the Airbnb app or phone. We provide full privacy during your stay and respond promptly to any questions or requests. Happy to share local dining recommendations and tips for exploring the area.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: For the safety of our guests, the address shown on the listing is NOT accurate. The exact address will be given once your stay is booked. Please note that this home is located in Koreatown, Los Angeles, 90005.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 4th guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 3 guests.\n\nPlease note: Guests must be at least 25 years old to book this property.",
