    tag: "Mountain",
    summary: "Nestled among towering cedar trees on a private 0.81-acre lot, this Swiss chalet-style cabin offers a secluded treehouse experience. \n\nThe warm, wood-clad interior is illuminated by skylights, and the cozy living area features a wood stove with a river rock hearth. \n\nThe kitchen boasts stainless steel appliances, butcher block countertops, and alder cabinetry. Both bedrooms provide spacious closets, and the remodeled bathroom showcases mid-century modern design.",
    description: "Enjoy year-round comfort with a mini-split system and dual-pane windows. \n\nWhat we offer? \n\n🛏 Comfortable & Spacious – This charming cabin offers a warm and inviting atmosphere with rustic wood accents, vaulted ceilings, and a cozy fireplace—perfect for chilly mountain evenings.\n\n🌲 Prime Location – Just minutes from Big Trees State Park, Bear Valley Ski Resort, and White Pines Lake, you'll have endless opportunities for hiking, skiing, fishing, and more. Plus, Arnold’s local shops, restaurants, and wineries are just a short drive away.\n\n🔥 Relax & Recharge – After a day of adventure, kick back on the spacious deck with stunning forest views, roast marshmallows by the fire pit, or enjoy a glass of wine under the stars.\n\n🏡 Home Away from Home – Fully stocked with all the essentials, including a well-equipped kitchen, cozy bedding, WiFi, and modern amenities, ensuring a comfortable and hassle-free stay.\n\n🍽️ Sarafina's Italian Kitchen \n\n✅ Snowshow Brewing Company, and El Vaquero Mexican \n\n✅ There are caves to visit, go to Mercer caverns vs. Moaning caverns, must see is town of Murphys about 15 min. away. \n\n✅ Shopping, great restaurants, wine tasting, bars, Calaveras Big trees State Park, Sierra Nevada Logging museum, Bear Valley Ski Resort, Arnold Rim Trail.\n\nGuest will have access to the entire cabin with everything in it.\n\nThe guest can contact us anytime via text, messages, or via Airbnb.\n\nLiving in Arnold means embracing a slower pace of life, surrounded by stunning natural beauty and a strong sense of community. Whether you’re looking for a weekend retreat, a vacation rental, or a full-time residence, this mountain town offers an unparalleled quality of life with year-round recreational opportunities.\n\n✅ Beach Access (HOA)\n\n✅ Walking distance to a lake.\n\n✅ Resort access begins in June. We do provide passes.\n\n✅ Bear Valley is 30-mins away.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 3rd guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 2 guests.",
