    price: 105,
    tag: "Florida",
    summary: "Welcome to your perfect getaway in beautiful Palm Beach Gardens! This stylish and comfortable home offers a relaxing retreat just minutes from the beach, golf courses, and world-class dining.\n\nWhether you're here for a family vacation, a golf weekend, or a relaxing stay by the coast, this home is the perfect place to unwind.\n\nBook your stay today and experience the best of Palm Beach Gardens!",
    description: "Our stylish and inviting home, where comfort meets modern simplicity. We take pride in offering a clean, fashionable, and thoughtfully designed space for our guests to enjoy.\n\n✅ Bright & Open Living Area – The open-concept design seamlessly connects the kitchen and living room, creating a warm and welcoming space perfect for family gatherings.\n\n✅ Cozy Sunroom Retreat – Unwind in our peaceful sunroom, an ideal spot to sip afternoon tea, read a book, or simply relax.\n\n✅ Expansive Backyard Oasis – Step outside to a lush, green backyard with plenty of space to enjoy the fresh air and outdoor activities.\n\n✅ Sparkling Pool & Sun Shelf – Whether you're taking a refreshing swim or lounging in the shallow sun shelf, our pool is perfect for fun and relaxation.\n\n✅ Comfortable & Practical Bedrooms – Rest easy in our cozy, thoughtfully designed bedrooms, ensuring a great night’s sleep.\n\nHere are some notable landmarks, restaurants, pubs, and tourist destinations nearby.\n\nLANDMARKS\n📍 The Gardens Mall – A premier shopping destination featuring over 160 specialty shops and restaurants, including high-end retailers like Saks Fifth Avenue and Nordstrom. \n\n📍 Worth Avenue – An upscale shopping and dining district in Palm Beach, renowned for its luxury boutiques, art galleries, and fine dining establishments. \n\n📍 Royal Poinciana Way Historic District – A historic area in Palm Beach featuring notable architectural structures, boutique shops, and dining options, reflecting the rich heritage of the region. \n\n\nRESTAURANTS\n📍 The Capital Grille – An upscale steakhouse known for its dry-aged steaks, fresh seafood, and extensive wine list, providing a refined dining experience.\n\n📍 Seasons 52 – A grill and wine bar offering a seasonal menu with fresh ingredients, complemented by an international selection of wines.\n\n📍 P.F. Chang's – A popular Asian-inspired restaurant serving a variety of dishes, including signature entrées and handcrafted cocktails.\n\nPUBS\n🍻 Yard House – A high-energy bar known for its extensive draft beer selection and a menu featuring American classics with a twist.\n\n🍻 The Brass Tap – A craft beer bar offering a wide variety of local and international brews, along with a menu of pub fare.\n\n🍻 Duffy's Sports Grill – A sports-themed bar and grill, perfect for catching a game while enjoying a selection of beers and American dishes.\n\nTOURIST SPOTS\n📍 CityPlace (Downtown West Palm Beach) – An upscale lifestyle center featuring a mix of shopping, dining, and entertainment options, set within Mediterranean and Venetian-inspired architecture. \n\n📍 John D. MacArthur Beach State Park – A natural preserve offering pristine beaches, kayaking, and nature trails, providing a glimpse into Florida's coastal ecosystems.\n\n📍 Norton Museum of Art – A renowned art museum in West Palm Beach, showcasing an extensive collection of American, European, and Chinese art.\n\nThese establishments and attractions offer a diverse range of experiences, from shopping and dining to cultural and outdoor activities, all within a convenient distance from the house.\n\nOur home is on a traditional Neighborhood in the city of Palm Beach Gardens, it is an open neighborhood so there is no HOA or gate entrance. \n\n🅿️PARKING🅿️\nThe home has a 7-car driveway, so plenty of space to park your vehicles!\n\nWe will be a text away! More than hosting you at our home we are here to give you advice on the best restaurants and locas spots for you to share and enjoy our home town!\n\nTraditional neighborhood in palm beach gardens! Middle working class but great energy and folks all around! Wonderful location close to everything!\n\nThe location is ideal! You have both high ways less than 3 minute away (turnpike & 95), Publix 2 min away, Gardens mall 5 min away, beach 10 min away, dog park 3 min away, Churches 3 min away, various parks around, and all the common fast food and restaurants less than 5 min away!\n\nWe want to make sure that your experience is magical! Therefore, we want to make sure guests know that it’s an older home, but fully remodeled and designed by us with much love for our guests. Perfect is hard to find, but we can promise to do our best to make your experience as good as possible!\n\n✅ For 3 weeks stays or longer, we do require a mid-stay cleaning. Cleaning fee is applicable.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 4th guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 3 guests.",
