    summary: "Whether you're visiting for game day, touring Auburn University, or simply enjoying the charm of this historic college town, our beautifully appointed home at Northgate Blvd is your perfect home base. Located just minutes from campus, Jordan-Hare Stadium, and downtown Auburn, this spot combines convenience, comfort, and Southern hospitality.",
    description: "🛏️ Comfortable & Spacious\nThis home features [insert number] cozy bedrooms and [insert number] modern bathrooms, with plush beds, soft linens, and plenty of space to relax after a day out in town.\n\n🍳 Fully Equipped Kitchen\nEnjoy home-cooked meals or game-day snacks in the fully stocked kitchen, complete with modern appliances, cookware, and a dining area perfect for gatherings.\n\n🛋️ Relax & Unwind\nThe open living area offers comfy seating, a smart TV for streaming your favorite shows, and plenty of natural light. Whether you're working remotely or kicking back with friends, you’ll feel right at home.\n\n🌳 Outdoor Space\nTake advantage of the backyard for some fresh air or an evening drink under the stars. [Optional: Add a detail like “Fire pit, grill, or outdoor seating area” if available.]\n\n📍 Prime Location\n\n🚶‍♂️ 5 minutes to Auburn University\n\n🏟️ Quick drive to Jordan-Hare Stadium\n\n☕ Close to local restaurants, cafes, and shops\n\n🛣️ Easy access to Hwy 280 for trips to Montgomery or Atlanta\n\n🎉 Perfect For:\nFamilies, alumni, prospective students, business travelers, or anyone seeking a comfortable and convenient Auburn stay.\n\nCraving a bite or a coffee? The home is close to downtown Auburn, where you’ll find a variety of local restaurants, bars, boutiques, and cozy cafés. From Southern comfort food to trendy brunch spots, there’s something nearby for everyone.\n\nOutdoor lovers will appreciate the proximity to Chewacla State Park, just a short drive away, where you can hike, bike, or simply unwind in nature.\n\nWith quick access to major roads like US-280 and I-85, you're also perfectly positioned for day trips to Montgomery, Columbus, or even Atlanta.\n\nGuests will have access to the amenities of the unit.\n\nGuest can contact us 24/7 via call, SMS, or in the Airbnb platforms.\n\nSituated in a quiet and welcoming residential area, our home offers the perfect blend of peace and proximity. This neighborhood is known for its tree-lined streets, friendly neighbors, and unbeatable location—just minutes from the heart of Auburn.\n\nYou’ll be just a short drive (or even a walk!) from Auburn University, making this the ideal spot for visiting families, prospective students, alumni, and fans coming in for game day. Jordan-Hare Stadium, the Auburn Arena, and other campus landmarks are right around the corner, so you’ll never miss a moment of the action.\n\nUber and Lyft are your best friends.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 4th guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 3 guests.",
