    description: "==RESTAURANTS==\nArmando’s Mexican Restaurant – 3.5 mi \nA long‑standing Tex‑Mex favorite in Meyerland, known for fajitas & margaritas \n\nPhat Eatery – 5 mi\nHighly rated for Malaysian street food in nearby Chinatown \n\nLe Jardinier – 7 mi \nUpscale French‑fusion fare at the Museum of Fine Arts \n\nXochi – 8 mi \nJames Beard‑nominated Mexican cuisine in downtown Houston \n\nBadolina Bakery – 7 mi\nDelightful Middle Eastern pastries in Rice Village \n\n\n==PUBS & BARS== \nRudyard's Pub – 6 mi\nA Montrose institution with darts, trivia & comedy nights \n\nThe Bull & Bear Tavern – 8 mi\nCozy spot on Westheimer serving craft cocktails & local brews \n\nPimlico Irish Pub – 8 mi \nClassic Irish pub fare on Westheimer \n\nMonkey’s Tail – 8 mi \nA spacious bar with a modern vibe and craft beers \n\nLittle Woodrow’s (EaDo) – 10 mi \nDog‑friendly outdoor bar in downtown, great for game nights \n\n\n==ATTRACTIONS==\nGerald D. Hines Waterwall Park – 10 mi\nStunning Uptown fountain surrounded by trees \n\nHouston Museum of Natural Science – 8 mi \nFamily‑favorite with dinosaur fossils & planetarium \n\nMuseum of Fine Arts, Houston (MFAH) – 7 mi\nRenowned art museum with rotating exhibits \n\nHouston Zoo – 8 mi\nA century‑old animal park located in Hermann Park \n\nBuffalo Bayou Park – 12 mi\n160‑acre greenway for hiking, biking & kayaking\n\nGuest will have access to the entire house during their stay and all of its amenities.\n\nGuests can contact us via Airbnb, SMS, or call during their stay.\n\nWelcome to the vibrant Westbury neighborhood of Houston! Nestled just minutes from the Texas Medical Center, the Galleria, and NRG Stadium, this residential area offers a perfect blend of suburban calm and city convenience. Known for its mature trees, spacious lots, and friendly vibe, Westbury is ideal for those who want peace and quiet without being far from the action. Enjoy nearby parks, diverse dining options, and easy access to major highways for seamless exploring around Houston.\n\nThe best way to get around the Westbury area in Houston is by car. Houston is a very car-centric city, and this neighborhood—while peaceful and residential—isn’t as walkable or transit-friendly as more central districts.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 4th guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 3 guests.",
