    summary: "Welcome to your cozy and modern home-away-from-home, just minutes from the heart of Edinburgh! ✨🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿\n\nPerfect for couples, families, friends, or working travelers — this stylish 2-bedroom flat has everything you need for a comfy stay.",
    description: "✨ Property Highlights:\n\n🛏️ 2 Spacious Double Bedrooms – One upstairs with balcony view into the living room\n\n🛋️ Bright Open-Plan Living Space – Lounge, dine, and relax in style\n\n📺 55\" Smart TV – Kick back and binge your favorite shows\n\n🍳 Fully Equipped Kitchen – Stove, oven, microwave, cookware & dining essentials\n\n🧺 In-Unit Washer & Dryer – Perfect for longer stays\n\n🚽 1 Full Bathroom + 1 Half WC/Powder Room – No queues for the toilet!\n\n🌿 Ground Floor Entry – Easy access\n\n📍 Prime Location – Explore Edinburgh With Ease:\n\n✅ 10 mins to Edinburgh Castle\n\n✅ 10 mins to Calton Hill & stunning city views\n\n✅ 8 mins to Princes Street – shopping & cafes galore\n\n✅ 10 mins to Edinburgh Playhouse\n\n✅ Walkable to local restaurants, pubs & supermarkets\n\n✅ Close to Royal Botanic Garden for peaceful walks\n\n🅿️ There is paid parking on the street. Evenings, nights, and weekends are not charged.\n\nWhether you're here for a weekend escape or a longer adventure, you'll love the convenience and charm of this central Edinburgh flat.\n\n📆 Book now and enjoy a relaxing stay with everything you need just around the corner!\n\nGuest can have the whole flat.\n\nYou can message us for any inquiries here on Airbnb.\n\nLocated just about one mile northeast of Edinburgh’s city centre, Broughton lies on the edge of the New Town, bordered by Leith Walk, Bellevue, Canonmills, and Pilrig Residences include classic Georgian and Victorian tenements and townhouses, often featuring high ceilings and generous room sizes\n\nBroughton Road is a stylish and energetic locale offering historical charm, dining and cultural appeal, and top-tier connectivity. Ideal for those who want the buzz of city life with leafy retreats close by. Let me know if you need details on rentals, local listings, or daily commuting!\n\n‼️IMPORTANT‼️\nThe studio is located in a vibrant, historic part of Edinburgh, and like many traditional buildings in the area, the entrance opens directly onto the pavement.\n\nGuest must use their own log-ins for any streaming services; we don't provide one.\n\n🅿️ PARKING INFO 🅿️\nStreet parking is available and it is free from 5:30 pm to 8:30 am, including Saturday and Sunday. It is otherwise metered at £3.80 per hr with a pay-and-display style ticket.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 3rd guest onwards. Base price only covers the first 2 guests.",
