    tag: "Lakefront",
    summary: "Lakefront retreat on White Lake, Michigan with private hot tub and direct lake access. Pet friendly - bring your furry friends! Perfect for families, couples, and weekend getaways.\n\nKayaking, swimming, and fishing right from the property. Enjoy sunset soaks in the hot tub and lakeside fire pit evenings. Near Pontiac, Auburn Hills, and Detroit metro. Close to Pine Knob Music Theatre, Great Lakes Crossing Outlets, and Oakland University. Free parking and high-speed WiFi.",
    description: "Welcome to our stunning property that promises a memorable stay filled with comfort and entertainment. Indoors and out, you’ll discover all that this gem has to offer.\n\n🤩 Backyard 🤩\n✦ Hot tub with a stunning view of the lake.\n✦ BBQ grill and covered outdoor dining area for memorable meals\n\n🚗 Parking Info\n✦ FREE parking in front of the house, up to 2 cars.\n\n🛏️ Sleep & Stay in Comfort\n✦ Bedroom 1 – King bed \n✦ Bedroom 2 – King bed\n✦ Bedroom 3 – 2 Twin Beds\n\n🧼 Bathroom1\n✦ 1 bathroom fully stocked w/ essentials\n\n🛋️ Living Room\n✦ Full-size Sleeper Sofa\n✦ 65\" Smart Roku TV w/ Netflix and streaming services using your own log-ins.\n✦ Cozy living area with entertainment for the whole family\n✦ Indoor Fireplace\n\n🍳 Full Kitchen\n- Fully equipped with modern appliances\n- Dedicated coffee station for your morning brew\n- Everything you need for culinary adventures\n\n🍽️Dining Area\n✦ Seats 6comfortably at a beautifully set table and with an amazing view of the lake\n✦ Airy ambiance perfect for dining and chatting\n\n📍 Nearby Attractions – Just Minutes Away!\n✅ Pontiac Lake State Recreation Area - 4 mi west | 3,745 acre park: trails, fishing, boating, swimming, equestrian riding and more!\n\n✅ Indian Springs Metropark - 9 mi northwest | 2,547 acre metropark with golf, maze, nature center, splash‑play and hiking/biking trails\n\n✅ White River Light Station Museum - 12 mi (near Whitehall) | Historic 1875 lighthouse converted to museum – climb to the top for lake views\n\n✅ Hess Hathaway Park - 3 mi | Community park with walking trails, playground, picnic areas and small farm animals—family‑friendly outing\n\n✅ For a splash of adventure, guests have the option to rent paddle boards, kayaks, or even enjoy a boat ride during their stay.\n\n\n🍴RESTAURANT & PUBS NEARBY🍺\n✅ Ripples of the Lakes Restaurant & Bar - 1.8mi\n✅ Dave & Amy’s Bar & Grill - 3mi\n✅ Billy’s Tip ’n Inn - 2.8mi\n✅ White Lake Brunch Ham & Corned Beef - 2.5mi\n✅ Applebee’s Grill + Bar - 3.5mi\n✅ Stella's Table - 3.0mi\n✅ Graceland. Wine Shoppe - 3mi\n\n🚣🏼‍♂️ TOYS AVAILABLE 🤩\n✅3 kayaks\n✅1 paddleboat\n✅1 paddleboard\nwater guns, noodles, corn hole, badminton and cards.\n\nGuests will have access to the entire house and all of its amenities.\n\nThis property is equipped with a smart lock, a camera that monitors the front of the house for safety and security purposes.\n\nGuest are allowed to fish on the property.\n\nSelf check-in via smart lock for flexible arrival. Our hosting team is available 24/7 via the Airbnb app or phone. We provide full privacy during your stay and respond promptly to any questions or requests. Happy to share local dining recommendations and tips for exploring the area.\n\nWhy locals choose Lakeside Drive:\n\nLakeside living with four‑season fun—lake in summer, hiking and skiing in winter.\n\nFlowing nature meets affordability.\n\nReady‑to‑move‑in homes full of local character.\n\nPet-thumbed, kid‑safe streets.\n\nA true Michigan “Up‑North” feel—yet just 35 minutes from inner Detroit\n\n𝘉𝘺𝘳𝘦𝘳 𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘯𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘥𝘰𝘨 𝘸𝘢𝘭𝘬𝘴? Yup. Lakeside Drive corks toward its own tiny peninsula on Oxbow Lake, meaning no cut‑through streets, minimal cars—and full privacy.\n\nDirect sandy shorelines & boat docks – most lakefront lots on Oxbow come with sandy swim spots (no chlorine in sight) and private docks. Paddleboards, pontoons, or straight‑off‑the‑deck dips are all a go.\n\nA 270‑acre playground – Oxbow Lake is a private all‑sports lake (think fishing, speed boats, kayaking), part of the Huron River chain that also links to Pontiac Lake (640 acres, public launch nearby).\n\nA real range of homes – ranches, bifocals to bungalows built 1950–1980, many updated with modern kitchens, lake-deck expansion, and lush private yards—lots typically ¼ to ¾ acre.\n\nSchool cluster = Huron Valley Schools – neighborhoods feed into Oxbow Elementary, White Lake Middle, and Lakeland High. The district consistently ranks among the top 30% in Michigan.\n\nHome values stay steady – median home value in 48386 sits in the upper $300Ks, with updated lakefronts trading anywhere from mid‑$400Ks to $700K+ depending on lot size and upgrades.\n\nNature-watchers, rejoice – deer, swans, herons, and turtles are neighborhood regulars. Summer mornings bring ducks; fall evenings reward long lake-fog sunsets.\n\nJust minutes to grocery & weekend brunch – pop onto M‑59 and you’re under 10 minutes from Kroger, ALDI, local cafés, Town Centre shops, and the seasonal farmer’s market.\n\nAll‑season accessibility – winter or spring, Lakeside Drive stays shovel-ready. Alpine Valley ski resort is close for snow tubing, and Oakland County bike trails are just a kick from your front walk.\n\nNo HOA, big community heart – there’s no gate or fees; instead neighbors gather at porch swing chats, backyard potlucks, kayak flotillas, or dockside campfire marshmallow tosses.\n\nNearby attractions:\n- White Lake waterfront activities (on-site)\n- Highland Recreation Area (10 min)\n- Proud Lake Recreation Area (15 min)\n- Pine Knob Music Theatre / DTE Energy (20 min)\n- Great Lakes Crossing Outlets (20 min)\n- Oakland University (20 min)\n- Pontiac / Auburn Hills (15 min)\n- Detroit metro (45 min)\n- Detroit Metro Airport (45 min)\n\nHot tub usage: $50/day fee (request if using).\nPet friendly.\n\nExtra guest fee: $20/guest per night from the 4th guest onwards. Base price covers first 3 guests.",
