    slug: "arroyo-ave-unit-302",
    name: "Chic Dallas 2BR w/ Rooftop & Ensuite Comfort",
    location: "Dallas, TX",
    price: 115,
    tag: "Unit",
    summary: "Modern 2BR Dallas condo with private rooftop deck and ensuite bathrooms. Minutes from Deep Ellum, Uptown, Downtown Dallas, and the Design District. Perfect for couples, business travelers, and small groups.\n\n3rd-floor unit with 2 spacious bedrooms, 3 full bathrooms, fully equipped kitchen, and high-speed WiFi. Rooftop deck ideal for morning coffee or evening skyline views. Near AT&T Stadium, American Airlines Center, SMU, and Baylor Medical Center. Free parking included.",
    description: "🍽️ Nearby Restaurants\nSachet – A Mediterranean-inspired eatery offering seasonal dishes like falafel sandwiches and chicken shawarma bowls. ​\n\nThe Landmark Restaurant – Located within the Warwick Melrose Hotel, this upscale spot serves classic American fare. ​\n\nThe Library – A cozy lounge known for its cocktails and intimate atmosphere, also situated in the Warwick Melrose Hotel. ​\n\nPanera Bread – Casual bakery-café offering soups, salads, and sandwiches.\n\n🏛️ Nearby Landmarks\nAmerican Airlines Center – A premier venue hosting major concerts and home games for the Dallas Mavericks and Dallas Stars. ​\n\nTurtle Creek Park – A serene urban park featuring walking trails and scenic views. ​\n\nDallas Contemporary – A modern art museum showcasing innovative and thought-provoking works. ​\n\n\nFreedman’s Cemetery Memorial – A historical site honoring the African American community in Dallas.\n\n🛒 Nearby Grocery Stores\nKroger – Cedar Springs Rd – A full-service grocery store offering fresh produce, meats, and more. ​\n\nTom Thumb – Lemmon Ave – A supermarket providing a wide selection of groceries and household items. ​\n\nAlbertsons – Dallas – A grocery chain offering fresh produce, meats, and bakery items.\n\nGuest will have access to the entire house during their stay.\n\nSelf check-in via smart lock for flexible arrival. Our hosting team is available 24/7 via the Airbnb app or phone. We provide full privacy during your stay and respond promptly to any questions or requests. Happy to share local dining recommendations and tips for exploring the area.\n\nNestled in the vibrant Oak Lawn neighborhood, this home places you in one of Dallas' most desirable and walkable areas. Just minutes from Uptown, Downtown, and the Medical District, you’ll enjoy easy access to restaurants, nightlife, shopping, and parks. The area blends charm and convenience with tree-lined streets, diverse dining, and cultural landmarks. Whether you're here for business or leisure, Oak Lawn offers a perfect mix of energy and relaxation.\n\nUber and Lyft will be your best bet if you're not driving.\n\nNearby attractions:\n- Deep Ellum nightlife and dining (5 min)\n- Uptown Dallas (5 min)\n- Downtown Dallas / Arts District (5 min)\n- AT&T Stadium / Globe Life Field (20 min)\n- American Airlines Center (10 min)\n- SMU campus (10 min)\n- Baylor Medical Center (5 min)\n- Katy Trail (1.8 mi walk/bike)\n- Dallas Market Center (0.7 mi)\n- Harry Hines DART Station (0.4 mi walk)\n- Design District galleries (5 min)\n\nHouse rules:\n- Quiet hours: 10 PM - 8 AM\n- No smoking, no parties\n- No street or lawn parking\n\nExtra guest fee: $20/guest per night from the 3rd guest onwards. Base price covers first 2 guests.",
