    price: 125,
    tag: "Florida",
    summary: "🌴 Welcome to Your West Palm Beach Getaway! 🌞\n\nStep into this bright and comfortable 1-bedroom apartment that sleeps up to 4 guests—perfect for couples, small families, or friends. The space is designed for both relaxation and convenience\n\nJust 8 minutes from the pristine shores of Palm Beach Island, this home offers both luxury and convenience. Discover your dream coastal lifestyle in this charming, well-appointed sanctuary.",
    description: "✨ What You’ll Love:\n\nA cozy bedroom + w pull out couch as extra bed to 4 guests\n\nHigh-speed Wi-Fi for work or streaming\n\nA fully equipped kitchen and living area for all your needs\n\nFresh, inviting décor that sets the tone for a relaxing stay\n\n📍 Location Highlights:\nYou’ll be close to local shops, dining, and West Palm Beach attractions—whether you’re here for the beaches, nightlife, or cultural spots like Clematis Street and Rosemary Square.\n\n🌟 Interesting Places Nearby\n\nNorton Museum of Art (0.7 mi) – Renowned collection of American, European & Chinese art.\n\nAnn Norton Sculpture Gardens (0.5 mi) – Peaceful gardens with unique sculptures.\n\nKravis Center (1.1 mi) – Broadway shows, concerts & cultural performances.\n\n🍴 Restaurants\n\nHullabaloo (1.3 mi) – Italian bites & craft cocktails.\n\nThe Regional Kitchen (1.2 mi) – Seasonal American flavors with a Southern twist.\n\nGrato (0.7 mi) – Wood-fired pizzas & Italian classics.\n\n🍺 Pubs & Nightlife\n\nRoxy’s Pub (1.5 mi) – Rooftop bar & lively vibe.\n\nO’Shea’s Irish Pub (1.4 mi) – Cozy Irish spot with beers & pub fare.\n\nCopper Blues (1.6 mi) – Rock-themed pub with live music.\n\n🛒 Grocery Stores\n\nPublix (3.9 mi) – Everyday essentials & fresh produce.\n\nWhole Foods (1.8 mi) – Organic & natural groceries.\n\nThe Fresh Market (8.6 mi) – Gourmet foods & specialty items.\n\nYour perfect spot to unwind, recharge, and explore everything West Palm Beach has to offer! 🌴✨\n\nYou'll have access to the entire place during your stay. Treat is as if it yours and have an amazing time!\n\nYou can contact us anytime via the Airbnb app or through our contact number.\n\nWelcome to the vibrant and picturesque neighborhood surrounding our home. Nestled in the heart of West Palm Beach, Florida. This charming area perfectly balances urban convenience with coastal tranquility, offering residents an idyllic lifestyle.\n\nHistoric Charm and Modern Amenities\nThe neighborhood is renowned for its historic charm, characterized by beautifully preserved homes and tree-lined streets. Architectural enthusiasts will appreciate the blend of classic Floridian and Mediterranean Revival styles. Despite its historic ambiance, the area is replete with modern amenities, ensuring a comfortable and contemporary living experience.\n\nProximity to Attractions\nResidents enjoy close proximity to an array of cultural and recreational attractions. The Norton Museum of Art and the Ann Norton Sculpture Gardens are just minutes away, offering rich cultural experiences. The Kravis Center for the Performing Arts is also nearby, providing world-class entertainment ranging from Broadway shows to classical music performances.\n\nDining and Nightlife\nThe culinary scene is vibrant and diverse, with trendy restaurants like Hullabaloo and upscale dining at The Regional Kitchen & Public House within easy reach. For a casual night out, locals can head to popular pubs such as Roxy’s Pub and O’Shea’s Irish Pub. These spots offer a lively atmosphere, making them perfect for socializing and unwinding.\n\nOutdoor Activities and Beaches\nOutdoor enthusiasts will love the area's access to beautiful parks and the pristine shores of Palm Beach Island, just an 8-minute drive away. The nearby waterfront offers opportunities for boating, fishing, and enjoying the stunning Atlantic Ocean vistas.\n\nShopping and Convenience\nGrocery shopping is a breeze with options like Whole Foods Market and Publix Super Market close by. Additionally, the vibrant Clematis Street and Rosemary Square offer a variety of shopping, dining, and entertainment options, ensuring that everything you need is within a short distance.\n\nCommunity and Lifestyle\nThe neighborhood fosters a strong sense of community, with friendly neighbors and a welcoming atmosphere. The fully-fenced backyards and pet-friendly policies make it an ideal location for families and pet owners. The local schools, parks, and community events contribute to a high quality of life, making it a sought-after area for both families and professionals.\n\n1. Car\nWest Palm Beach is easily navigable by car and have convenient access to major roadways such as I-95 and US-1. With ample parking available in the neighborhood and surrounding areas, exploring the city and beyond is a breeze.\n\n2. Public Transportation\nFor those who prefer public transportation, Palm Tran operates bus services throughout West Palm Beach and the surrounding areas. Bus stops are conveniently located within walking distance of the house providing easy access to key destinations and transit hubs.\n\n3. Biking and Walking\nThe neighborhood's pedestrian-friendly streets and dedicated bike lanes make biking and walking popular modes of transportation. Residents can enjoy leisurely strolls or bike rides to nearby parks, restaurants, and attractions while soaking in the area's scenic beauty.\n\n4. Ride-Sharing and Taxis\nRide-sharing services such as Uber and Lyft are readily available in West Palm Beach, providing convenient transportation options for you during your stay! Taxis are also accessible for those who prefer traditional transportation methods.\n\n5. Nearby Airports\nFor air travel, Palm Beach International Airport (PBI) is conveniently located just a short drive away from the neighborhood. This major airport offers domestic and international flights, providing residents with convenient access to global destinations.\n\n📌 Note: Extra guest fee of $20/guest per night applies from the 2nd guests onwards. Base price only covers the 1st guest.",
