    tag: "Beachfront",
    summary: "Welcome to your private slice of paradise in Vero Beach! \n\nNestled beneath canopy of oaks and bordered by the Coastal Oaks Preserve and Harmony Oaks Conservation Area, this home offers direct access to the Indian River Lagoon with a private dock where manatees surface as you fish steps from your door. \n\nIn the desirable Vero Shores enclave, it’s equidistant from downtown Vero Beach and Fort Pierce, offering easy access to dining, shopping, and entertainment amid tranquil lagoon life.",
    description: "✨ Waterfront Escape on the Indian River – See Manatees from Your Dock! ✨\n\nStep inside this bright and airy home designed for both comfort and connection. The living room offers plenty of space to relax, while the fully equipped kitchen makes cooking easy—whether it’s a family breakfast or snacks before the beach. The split floor plan ensures privacy, with a master suite on one side and two guest bedrooms with a full bath down the hall. A washer and dryer keep swimsuits and towels fresh throughout your stay.\n\n🌴 Outdoor Paradise\n 🏊‍♂️ Saltwater pool (8ft deep, not heated)\n🍹 Tiki bar for cocktails\n🍖 Grill & dine poolside \n🚻 Outdoor bath & shower for easy poolside use\n🌊 Peaceful water views for manatee watching & private dock for fishing & sunrise coffee\n\n🍴 Eat & Drink\n\n• Upscale Oceanfront dining: Ocean Grill, Citrus Grillhouse, Cobalt\n• Local icons: 12A Bouy, Skipper’s Cove, Little Jim’s\n• Casual favorites: Twisted Lime, The Green  Marlin, Casey’s Burgers\n• ☕ Dunkin’ just down the road\n\n🛍️ Shop & Stock Up\n\n• Publix & Fresh Market- everyday groceries close by\n• Ft. Pierce Farmers Market, #1 Market in Florida– Saturday mornings with, souvenirs, local produce, food & live music\n• The Beach Shop- Fun store for souvenirs, high-quality clothing & swimsuits\n• Vero Beach Outlets – favorite brands like Michael Kors & Coach\n\nExperience Vero Beach\n\n🎣 Professional Outfitters & Fishing Tackle – stock up for your fishing adventures\n🌸 McKee Botanical Gardens – stroll through lush tropical landscapes\n⚓ Navy Seal Museum – explore fascinating history\n🚤 Riverside Park & MacWilliams Boat Launch – perfect for picnics or getting out on the water\n🍷 Summer Crush Winery – sip local wines & enjoy outdoor concerts\n\nYou can access the entire place.\n\nWe love to communicate to our guests here on Airbnb! Just message us if you have further questions.\n\n🌴 Perfectly Located in Vero Beach! Just minutes from sandy beaches, local cafés, and oceanfront dining. Publix and The Fresh Market are nearby for easy grocery runs, while shops, outlets, and charming historic spots are all a short drive away. Whether you’re here for sunshine, shopping, or seaside relaxation, everything you need is close by! 🌞🍹\n\nBordered by the Coastal Oaks Preserve and Harmony Oaks Conservation Area, residents enjoy scenic trails and peaceful habitats filled with native Florida wildlife. 🌿🦋 The neighborhood’s charm lies in its blend of longtime residents and new families, creating a community that feels both established and welcoming.\n\nThe neighborhood offers both inland and waterfront properties, with deep canals that flow directly into the Indian River and Intracoastal Waterway. It’s a true haven for boaters, fishermen, and nature lovers—where spotting manatees right from your backyard is part of everyday life. 🐾🐟\n\n🚗 Getting Around Vero Beach is a breeze! Most shops, grocery stores, and restaurants are just a few minutes away by car. Parking is easy and convenient at the home. 🚲 Want to explore like a local? Bike rentals and rideshares (Uber/Lyft) are available, and the beach is only a short drive for sun, sand, and ocean views. 🌊☀️\n\n📌 Please Note\n\n👥 Extra Guests: $20 per person, per night from the 4th guest onward (base rate covers 3 guests).\n\n🕰️ Early check-in and late check out request is subject to approval and availability. A $25 fee is applicable for 2:30pm check in and 10:30am check out.\n\n🐾 Pets: One small dog under 35 lbs is welcome. Sorry, no cats or other animals permitted.\n\n🚤 Boats: Guest boats may be parked in the driveway/front of the property, but docking is not allowed. The boat currently docked belongs to the owner and is strictly off-limits.\n\n🎥 Security: Exterior cameras face the dock for safety. Boarding, tampering with, or attempting to use the owner’s boat is prohibited and will result in fines.\n\n🧴 Essentials: Guests are responsible for personal toiletries (paper towels & toilet paper provided).\n\n🔥 Grill & Fire Pit: Guests are responsible for refilling the propane tank if it runs out.\n\n🥂 Pool Safety: Absolutely no glass in or around the pool area. If glass enters the pool, guest will be fined.\n\n🚪 Doors & Windows: Please keep all doors and windows closed. Open windows/doors for extended periods cause extreme indoor humidity levels.\n\n🦟 Insects: Florida is tropical! Bring bug spray or a Thermacell device so mosquitoes or other insects don’t interfere with your stay.",
