    summary: "Canal-side 2BR home in Siesta Key Village, Sarasota. Walk to Siesta Key Beach, voted #1 beach in the USA. One block from Siesta Village shops, restaurants, and bars. Sleeps 6 - perfect for beach vacations, couples, and family getaways.\n\nFish right from your backyard canal. Free trolley and cab access to explore the island without a car. Near St. Armands Circle, Downtown Sarasota, Lido Beach, and Sarasota-Bradenton Airport. BBQ grill, bikes, and free parking included.",
    description: "Neighborhood Highlights:\n✔️ 5-min walk to Siesta Key Beach – voted #1 Beach in the USA\n✔️ 1 block from Siesta Village – shops, Morton’s Grocery, bars & restaurants\n✔️ Hop on the free Siesta Key trolley or cabs for easy island exploring\n\nHome Highlights:\n🛌 2 bedrooms – each with a queen bed & TV\n\n🛋️ Living room – sofa bed with hybrid air & spring mattress + loveseat pull-out (great for kids)\n\n🥘 Fully equipped kitchen – stove, oven, microwave, fridge, coffee maker, and all cooking essentials\n\n🛀🏻 1 bathroom – clean and convenient\n\n🧺 Shared Washer & dryer – for easy laundry\n\n🍃 Shared Waterfront & Backyard – BBQ grill + outdoor seating for evening hangouts\n\n🚲 Shared Bikes available – adult & kids’ bikes ready for island rides\n\n🌼 Shared amenities also includes – beach gears like chairs, umbrellas, toys and carts.\n\nThe perfect retreat for couples, families, or small groups who want the beach, the village, and the island lifestyle—all in one stay!\n\nYou'll have access to the entire place during your stay.\n\nSelf check-in via smart lock for flexible arrival. Our hosting team is available 24/7 via the Airbnb app or phone. We provide full privacy during your stay and respond promptly to any questions or requests. Happy to share local dining recommendations and tips for exploring the area.\n\n🌴 Neighborhood Highlights\n\nStaying here means you’re right in the heart of Siesta Key Village—everything is just a short walk or a quick ride away:\n\n🏖 Siesta Key Beach (0.4 miles / 5-min walk)\nVoted the #1 Beach in the USA, famous for its soft white quartz sand and turquoise waters—perfect for swimming, sunbathing, or catching a sunset.\n\n🛍 Siesta Key Village (1 block away)\nThe lively center of the island with Morton’s Grocery, boutique shops, beachwear stores, coffee spots, and ice cream parlors.\n\n🍽 Bars & Restaurants\nEnjoy everything from fresh seafood and casual bites to cocktail bars and live music—all within walking distance.\n\n🚲 Outdoor Fun\nRent paddleboards, kayaks, or jet skis nearby. Or just hop on the bikes provided at the house for a relaxing ride around the island.\n\n🚐 Getting Around\n\nFree Siesta Key Breeze Trolley: Runs daily along the island—hop on and off to explore beaches, shops, and restaurants at no cost.\n\nFree local cabs: Quick and convenient for short trips around the Key.\n\nWalking & Biking: The village and beach are so close you can skip the car and enjoy the fresh island air.\n\nCar Access: If you plan to explore beyond the island, downtown Sarasota is only about a 15-minute drive.\n\nNearby attractions:\n- Siesta Key Beach / #1 Beach in USA (walk)\n- Siesta Key Village shops and dining (1 block)\n- St. Armands Circle (10 min)\n- Lido Beach (10 min)\n- Downtown Sarasota (15 min)\n- Marie Selby Botanical Gardens (15 min)\n- Mote Marine Laboratory (10 min)\n- Sarasota-Bradenton Airport (25 min)\n\nFree trolley available on the island. Bikes and BBQ grill provided.\n\nExtra guest fee: $20/guest per night from the 3rd guest onwards. Base price covers first 2 guests.",
