    description: "🏡 This spacious 4BR/2BA retreat sleeps up to 10 comfortably and is designed with groups in mind—whether you’re here for family fun, FSU game days 🏈, or a weekend getaway with friends.\n\n★ Living Room ★\n\n⋑ Cozy living room with all your essentials\n⋑ Ceiling fan to keep you cool\n⋑ Plush couches for ultimate relaxation\n⋑ TV for entertainment\n⋑ Beautiful hanging frames adding a touch of elegance\n⋑ Fun board games for family and friends\n⋑ Window with room-darkening shades for privacy and comfort\n⋑ Fun foosball table for friendly competition\n\n★ Full Kitchen ★\n\n⋑ Kitchen island with bar seating for 4\n⋑ Gorgeous hardwood floors\n⋑ Fully equipped and spacious for all your culinary needs\n⋑ Ample cupboards for storage\n⋑ Dedicated coffee station for your morning boost\n⋑ Modern appliances to make cooking a breeze\n\n★ Dining Room ★\n\n⋑ Dining table with 4 seats and bench seating (can seat 6)\n⋑ Direct access to the outdoor area\n⋑ Just steps away from the living room\n\n\n★ Bedrooms ★\n\n⋑ Master Bedroom: King bed, dedicated workspace, en suite bathroom\n⋑ Bedroom 2: Queen bed, standing mirror, window with room-darkening shades\n⋑ Bedroom 3: Beautiful decor, wardrobe storage\n⋑ Bedroom 4: 2 single beds, window with curtains\n\n★ Bathrooms ★\n\n⋑ 2 full bathrooms\n⋑ Master’s bathroom: Bathtub, shower, his and hers sink, window with room-darkening shades\n⋑ Bathroom 2: Bathtub/shower combo\n⋑ Hygiene essentials and towels provided\n\n★ Outdoor ★\n\n⋑ Large backyard with 2 al fresco dining areas\n⋑ Corn hole game for outdoor fun\n⋑ Backyard patio with fire pit for cozy evenings\n⋑ Relaxing hammock among beautifully lined trees\n⋑ Cozy lounge seating on the patio and giant connect 4\n⋑ BBQ grill for cookouts\n⋑ Porch with plush seating for relaxing moments\n\n\n📍 Nearby Destinations & Distances\n\nFlorida State University / Doak Campbell Stadium 🏟️ – ~5.5 miles\n\nPublix at Forest Village Shopping Center 🛒 – ~4.5 miles\n\nTrader Joe’s 🥑 – ~5.5 miles\n\nGovernor’s Square Mall 🛍️ – ~6 miles\n\nCascades Park 🌳 – ~6.5 miles\n\nTom Brown Park 🚴 – ~7 miles\n\nGuest will have access to the entire house and all of its amenities.\n\nThis property is equipped with a smart lock, front door Ring doorbell camera, and noise monitor (as required by Fort Lauderdale regulations).\n\nSelf check-in via smart lock for flexible arrival. Our hosting team is available 24/7 via the Airbnb app or phone. We provide full privacy during your stay and respond promptly to any questions or requests. Happy to share local dining recommendations and tips for exploring the area.\n\nNestled in a quiet & safe residential area, this home offers a peaceful retreat while being conveniently close to everything you’ll want. \n\nMinutes from Highway 10, giving easy access to shopping, restaurants, and main routes across town. \n\nThe area feels suburban and family-friendly, with plenty of natural light, green spaces, and well-maintained homes.\n\nPeaceful surroundings with easy access to all that Tallahassee has to offer.\n\n🏛 Downtown Tallahassee – ~10 mins: Explore restaurants, shops, and cultural spots.\n\n🏈 Florida State University & Doak Campbell Stadium – ~15 mins: Perfect for visiting students or catching a game day.\n\n🌳 Cascades Park – ~10 mins: A beautiful spot for walking, concerts, and outdoor activities.\n\n🛍 Governor’s Square Mall – ~8 mins: Shopping, dining, and entertainment in one place.\n\n✈️ Tallahassee International Airport – ~20 mins: Convenient for travelers.\n\nWith nearby highways, local dining, and everyday essentials just minutes away, you’ll enjoy both comfort and convenience throughout your stay.\n\nNearby attractions:\n- Florida State University / Doak Campbell Stadium (10 min)\n- FAMU campus (15 min)\n- Downtown Tallahassee / Capitol Building (15 min)\n- Cascades Park (12 min)\n- Wakulla Springs State Park (30 min)\n- Tallahassee Mall and shops (5 min)\n\nHouse rules:\n- Quiet hours: 10 PM - 8 AM (city enforced)\n- No smoking inside the property\n- No parties or events\n- No street or lawn parking\n- No garage access\n- $300 minimum fee for house rule violations\n\nExtra guest fee: $20/guest per night from the 5th guest onwards. Base price covers first 4 guests.",
